name: **Annaghvaan – Eanach Mheáin**
description: Annaghvaan – Eanach Mheáin L912-299 Sheet 44 Essentially the road bridge to Lettermore and Gorumna, the road passing along its SE side, Annaghvaan has its own community of its own people on its low lying terrain. Tides The passage immediately S of the island (SW to Lettermore) has extensive drying areas at LW. Bealadangan pass to the SE may be a better bet, but watch the strength of the current.
